  "body": "> The current code returns immediately if there is no inbound connection; this change just allows control to flow past the handshake piece.\r\n\r\n> As to why the code isn't doing a handshake for inbound connections: no idea, but if I had to guess it would be that the outbound peer always initiates the handshake so the inbound doesn't need to do so as well.\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @mcdee in https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/pull/4173_\r\n\r\nThis looks like an existing issue discoverd in @mcdee's PR. Filing an issue so we can capture this.",
